Seven others were killed in separate incidents in the Polokwane Makhado &amp; Roedtan areas. JOHANNESBURG Twelve people have been killed in a crash between a taxi and a truck near Mokopane, bringing to 23 the number of people killed in that province in separate road accidents at the weekend. On Saturday, four people died when the vehicles they were travelling in collided head on the N1 in Musekene. Seven others were killed in separate incidents in the Polokwane Makhado and Roedtan areas. The police s Moatshe Ngoepe says, A total of 23 people have died during various road accidents between Saturday evening and this morning. All in all in this incident we ve opened a case of culpable homicide and we re still investigating. 